      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Compound <b>A</b> (C<sub>9</sub>H<sub>12</sub>) absorbed 3 equivalents of H<sub>2</sub> on catalytic reduction over a palladium catalyst to give <b>B</b> (C<sub>9</sub>H<sub>18</sub>). On ozonolysis, compound <b>A</b> gave, among other things, a ketone that was identified as cyclohexanone. On treatment with NaNH<sub>2</sub> in NH<sub>3</sub>, followed by addition of iodomethane, compound <b>A</b> gave a new hydrocarbon, <b>C</b> (C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>14</sub>). What are the structures of <b>A</b>, <b>B</b>, and <b>C</b>?",
